The paper deals with information theory, specifically entropy and rate-distortion functions, which suggests cs.IT and cs.ITP as likely categories. The use of convex geometry in the proof technique also suggests cs.DS as a possible category. The study of channel capacity and noise channels suggests cs.SI as a possible category. Finally, the study of random vectors suggests cs.MS as a possible category.
